  "prompt": "How resources are allocated in the union budget?",
  "response": "In the Union Budget of India, resources are allocated through a systematic process:\n\n1. Revenue Sources:\n- Tax revenues (direct and indirect taxes)\n- Non-tax revenues\n- Borrowings\n- Disinvestment proceeds\n\n2. Allocation Mechanism:\n- Parliamentary approval\n- Demands for grants from various ministries\n- Budget proposals by Finance Ministry\n- Prioritizing national development goals\n\n3. Major Expenditure Categories:\n- Revenue expenditure\n- Capital expenditure\n- Plan and non-plan expenditure\n- Developmental and non-developmental spending\n\n4. Allocation Principles:\n- Constitutional mandates\n- Economic priorities\n- Social welfare objectives\n- Sectoral development needs\n\n5. Budget Allocation Process:\n- Line ministries submit budget proposals\n- Finance Ministry reviews and finalizes allocations\n- Cabinet approves final budget\n- Parliament discusses and sanctions budget\n\n6. Key Focus Areas:\n- Infrastructure development\n- Social sector schemes\n- Defense\n- Education\n- Healthcare\n- Agriculture\n- Rural development\n\n7. Budgetary Mechanisms:\n- Consolidated Fund of India\n- Contingency Fund\n- Public Account\n\nThe allocation process ensures balanced and strategic resource distribution across different sectors and developmental priorities.",
